<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Structure on 忍ばない怠惰テックノート</title><link>/series/structure/</link><description>Recent content in Structure on 忍ばない怠惰テックノート</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>ja</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2025 23:00:00 -0300</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/series/structure/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Taxonomies Support</title><link>/features/taxonomies-support/</link><pubDate>Mon, 24 Mar 2025 23:00:00 -0300</pubDate><guid>/features/taxonomies-support/</guid><description>&lt;p>The main taxonomy in the theme is &lt;code>tags&lt;/code>, as it is the one listed under the title in every &amp;ldquo;single&amp;rdquo; page, but it&amp;rsquo;s also possible to set any number of arbitrary taxonomies which will be listed in the side pane details section.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For example, in this site there&amp;rsquo;s the taxonomies &lt;code>topic&lt;/code> and &lt;code>series&lt;/code> as defined in the config file.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-toml" data-lang="toml">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>[&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">taxonomies&lt;/span>]
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">tag&lt;/span> = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;tags&amp;#39;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">topic&lt;/span> = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;topics&amp;#39;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">series&lt;/span> = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;series&amp;#39;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div></description></item></channel></rss>